hopobject.body: A book of First Class stamps is there an over the counter flomax The film manages to be exhaustive without being exhausting. Reich and director Jacob Kornbluth cover an astounding amount of ground. Starting with the expected rundown of troubling facts and figures, the film expands outward to an array of hot topics that many audiences may not see coming: the decline of unions, the rise of women in the workforce, campaign finance, K Street lobbyists, falling income tax rates, the Occupy and Tea Party movements, and where iPhone parts are manufactured, to name a few.
